had owned. Visiting with animals can help people feel less depressed and can provide a welcome change from one's routine. People often become more active and responsive both during and after visiting with animals. Additionally, an animal visit can offer entertainment or a welcome distraction from pain and infirmity. So, don't be surprised if you run into some four-legged friends while walking down the halls of our hospital, they are there to cheer our patients and brighten their day! If you would like more information regarding pet therapy or joining the volunteers at Abilene Regional Medical Center please call the Volunteer office at 428-4953. Becoming A Volunteer To become a Volunteer at Abilene Regional… Complete an application and send the form to: Volunteer Coordinator Abilene Regional Medical Center 6250 Hwy 83/84 Abilene, TX, 79606 Make an appointment with the Volunteer Coordinator. Once approved, the following are required:
    Procedure: Orientation Drug Screening Have TB skin test (free) and follow up yearly Complete Training for assignment/department, sign in procedure, etc. Have ID photo taken for badge Once above is completed, see Volunteer Coordinator to pick up Volunteer jacket, photo badge, meet assigned supervisor of assigned area and begin on start date Shifts: Most Volunteers hours are scheduled 8 a.m. – 12 noon and/or 12 noon – 4 p.m. Monday through Friday. Some volunteers work on special projects, not shift hours, but actual time is determined by the type of assignment resulting from need and/or volunteer’s interests, abilities or talents. Benefits for Volunteers A volunteer uniform will be provided For each shift served, you will receive 1 meal in the hospital cafeteria A free flu shot will be offered once a year Complimentary Senior Circle membership offered to volunteers age 50+ Discount to the hospital gift shop Annual Holiday party Recognition during National Volunteer Week Plus: Gain a sense of purpose and meaning with… Numerous opportunities to assist others and help meet the needs of Abilene Regional Medical Center. A great chance to make new friends in a pleasant, friendly atmosphere. A wonderful outlet to increase physical and mental well-being by working and serving the community. Lend a hand. If you’re passionate about community service, care deeply for people and have the time and energy, we’d love to have your help at Abilene Regional Medical Center. Volunteering opportunities are available in various departments throughout our hospital. Get in touch, and let’s talk about how we can help each other. Download the adult volunteer services application and SEND to: Volunteer Coordinator Abilene Regional Medical Center 6250 Hwy 83/84 Abilene, TX, 79606 Volunteers at Abilene Regional Medical Center can choose to serve in any of the following areas: Lobby Desk at Main Entrance Women's Center Lobby Desk ICU Waiting Rooms Outpatient/Day Surgery Patient Relations (news