    .visitors-content-container { display:block !important;} {0} Community , Press Press Releases Press Topics Jenna Bush Hager to speak at Healthy Woman 6th Anniversary ABILENE,TX - Author, teacher and national news correspondent Healthy Woman will deliver keynote address at Healthy Woman’s 6th Anniversary. Hager will share her inspiration and powerful experiences, as the daughter and grand-daughter of former United States presidents, contributing correspondent on NBC’s Today Show and former chair of UNICEF’s Next Generation. "Abilene Regional Medical Center is exceedingly proud to bring Jenna Bush Hager to Abilene," said Amanda Maikranz, Healthy Woman Coordinator. "Healthy Woman programs are designed to empower women with the knowledge and confidence to make informed health care and well-being decisions, and I believe Jenna wholeheartedly embodies this mission." The event is open to both men and women and will be held on Tuesday, April 15 at 6:00 p.m. at the Abilene Civic Center. Tickets go on sale March 10. For ticket or sponsorship visit AbileneRegional.com . For additional information contact Amanda Maikranz at (325) 428-4952 or by email . About Jenna Bush Hager: Jenna Hager is a contributing correspondent on NBC’s Today show and an editor-at-large for Southern Living magazine. She is the author of The New York Times bestseller Ana’s Story: A Journey of Hope, which she wrote after traveling to Latin America in 2006 as an intern with UNICEF. Ana’s Story is based on the life of a 17-year-old single mother with HIV, who struggles to shield her child from the life she had of abuse and neglect. Hager remains involved with UNICEF and is currently the chair of its Next Generation initiative, which is dedicated to reducing childhood deaths around the world. Hager holds a bachelor’s degree in English from the University of Texas at Austin. She is also co-author of the children’s book Read All About It! Hager is the daughter of former U.S. President George W. Bush and First Lady Laura Bush. In 2008, she married Henry Hager. On April 13, 2013, she gave birth to daughter Margaret Laura "Mila" Hager. About Healthy Woman: Healthy Woman is an educational program provided by Abilene Regional Medical Center. It is designed to empower women with the knowledge and confidence to make informed health care and well-being decisions for themselves and their loved ones. About ARMC: Abilene Regional Medical Center is a 231-bed, full service, all private-room acute care hospital where technology and skilled professionals come together to provide compassionate, customer-focused care. Key services include an Emergency Department with a 30 Minutes or Less ER Service Pledge, Accredited Chest Pain Center, Women’s Services, Orthopedics, Cardiology, Wound Care Center, Neurology, Skilled Nursing Unit, Cardiac Rehab, Wellness Center and the area’s only Neonatal Intensive Care Unit and robot-assisted surgical system. With more than 200 physicians and 800 employees, Abilene Regional Medical Center is committed to serving your healthcare needs. #cpsys_FormItem_DocDirectory1_TaxonomySpecialtyDD {width:260px;}
